  "prompt": "What constitutes as a good small group question/topic?",
  "response": "A good small group question or topic has several key characteristics. It should be:\n\n1. **Open-ended**: Allows for discussion and multiple viewpoints rather than a simple yes or no answer.\n2. **Relevant**: Connects with the interests, experiences, or knowledge of the group members.\n3. **Thought-provoking**: Encourages critical thinking and deeper analysis.\n4. **Appropriate**: Takes into consideration the group's background, age, and familiarity with the subject.\n5. **Engaging**: Captures the interest of the participants and keeps them invested in the conversation.\n\nExamples of good small group questions/topics include:\n- How can we balance work and personal life effectively?\n- What steps can we take to promote sustainability in our community?\n- How has technology changed the way we communicate?\n- What is the impact of social media on our mental health?\n- How can we address the issue of inequality in education?\n\nThese types of questions/topics foster interaction, encourage diverse perspectives, and create meaningful dialogue among participants.",
